parameters: \n<Station Attendant>.........! Um... are you okay?
\n<White-haired Detective>\N[3]-san! \N[3]-san! Are you okay?!
Actor03
\n<\N[3]>This place...! The device...!
\n<White-haired Detective>The device...? Um, are you really okay?
Actor03
\n<\N[3]>Uh... Ah... I'm fine... Where am I...?

\n<White-haired Detective>We're at Sakuhai Station. I heard from the station
attendant that you collapsed inside the station,
so I rushed over... What happened?
Actor03

\n<\N[3]>...I was investigating...on the train... No,
underground...

\n<White-haired Detective>Underground... Ah, that's right! I had received
testimony that there is a huge facility
underground at this station, and I was planning to
inform you about it.

\n<White-haired Detective>It seems that until last night, signals were being
emitted from a device in that facility, but this
morning, it disappeared as if nothing had
happened.
Actor03
\n<\N[3]>Ah... I see... Well, that's a relief then...

\n<White-haired Detective>...Relief? No, with that, I will contact the
station management company and proceed with the
search of the underground facility...
Actor03

\n<\N[3]>...Well, there's no need to hurry so much. Most
likely, the phenomenon of people going insane
should stop by now.
\n<White-haired Detective>...Are you really okay...?

And so, the phenomenon of \c[2]people going
insane\c[0] that plunged Sakuhai City into chaos
drastically decreased in reported cases from that
day onwards.

After that, I was scheduled to undergo
questioning, but even if I were to explain the
events of that night, no one would understand.

The search for the underground facility ultimately
revealed that it had already been filled with
concrete, and shortly thereafter the search was
called off.
